    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-06T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5823: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-06T15:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6, 12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3500. My 3481, December 2, 4 p.m. I am informally advised by Foreign Office that
                        <persName>O’Grady</persName> has received not only reiterated instructions
                        <pb facs="0243" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> to confine his discussions to
                    matters concerning exchange of prisoners but also to refuse even to listen to
                    any representations on any other whatsoever.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
